  "notes": [
    "This configuration resolves City of Goodyear zoning by intersecting runtime coordinates with Layer 3 of the official public Obligations feature service.",
    "The official layer publishes ZoningType as an integer-coded domain; codedValueMappings translates every published domain value into its jurisdiction zoning code and description.",
    "The configured test coordinate at Goodyear Ballpark resolves to coded value 13, PAD, Planned Area Development.",
    "PAD is a separate raw attribute in this layer and is not the base zoning code; it contains an internal coded flag associated with planned-area records.",
    "Case_No, MAP_NO, ORD_NO, OpenTextURL, and GYID are retained when published because they may identify the governing zoning action or source document.",
    "Goodyear has approved a comprehensive Zoning Ordinance update scheduled to take effect August 5, 2026; the coded-value domain and this mapping must be reverified after that effective date.",
    "A resolved zoning result supports permit research but does not replace review of applicable PAD documents, cases, ordinances, stipulations, overlays, or confirmation by the City of Goodyear."
  ]
